  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. However, when determining the appropriate sentence, I must weigh both mitigating and aggravating factors. The defendant has no prior criminal record and has already made partial restitution, indicating remorse and a willingness to make amends. The spectator's outburst demanding 10 years is legally irrelevant and vastly disproportionate for a first-time, non-violent white-collar offense of this magnitude. Taking into account the need for punishment, deterrence, and rehabilitation, a brief period of incarceration followed by probation to ensure full restitution is appropriate.",
